a.title: ― isDefinedBy: Data structure component is defined by zero to one represented variable.
a.xlink:title: ― isDefinedBy: Data structure component is defined by zero to one represented variable.

a.title: ― isBasedOn: The represented variable that can be shared by multiple instance variables. Indicates comparability in substantive representation, universe, and (indirectly) conceptual domain. If a relationship to a represented variable is defined there should be no relationship to a conceptual variable.
a.xlink:title: ― isBasedOn: The represented variable that can be shared by multiple instance variables. Indicates comparability in substantive representation, universe, and (indirectly) conceptual domain. If a relationship to a represented variable is defined there should be no relationship to a conceptual variable.

a.title: ― isBasedOn: The conceptual variable that can be shared by a set of represented variables. Indicates comparability in conceptual domain and unit type.
a.xlink:title: ― isBasedOn: The conceptual variable that can be shared by a set of represented variables. Indicates comparability in conceptual domain and unit type.

a.title: ― measures: The defined class of people, entities, events, or objects to be measured by the represented variable.
a.xlink:title: ― measures: The defined class of people, entities, events, or objects to be measured by the represented variable.

a.title: ― takesSentinelValuesFrom: A represented variable may have more than one sets of sentinel value domains, one for each type of software platform on which related instance variables might be instantiated. All of the sentinel value domains must have sentinel conceptual domains that correspond exactly. This allows codes for missing values to be explicitly matched across platforms.
a.xlink:title: ― takesSentinelValuesFrom: A represented variable may have more than one sets of sentinel value domains, one for each type of software platform on which related instance variables might be instantiated. All of the sentinel value domains must have sentinel conceptual domains that correspond exactly. This allows codes for missing values to be explicitly matched across platforms.

a.title: ― takesSubstantiveValuesFrom: The substantive representation (substantive value domain) of the variable. This is equivalent to the relationship "Measures" in the Generic Statistical Information Model (GSIM) although GSIM makes no distinction between substantive and sentinel values.

a.title: ― takesSentinelConceptsFrom: Identifies the conceptual domain containing the set of sentinel concepts used to describe the conceptual variable.
